<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4c.65.4" />

<fw type="curatorial">4</fw>

<opener>
<dateline>
5835 Vine Street<lb/>
Lincoln, Nebraska 68505<lb/>
January 17, 1973
</dateline>

<address>
<addrLine>Mr. Mark A. Young</addrLine>
<addrLine>Public Information</addrLine>
<addrLine>South Dakota Bicentennial Comission</addrLine>
<addrLine>State Captitol</addrLine>
<addrLine>Pierre, South Dakota 57501</addrLine>
</address>

<salute>Dear Mr. Young:</salute>
</opener>
<p>I have your letter of January 19, 1973, asking permission to quote from BLACK ELK SPEAKS in your bicentennial pageant.</p>

<p>So far as I am concerned, I would be willing for you to quote from any of my work, giving proper credit. But first I think you should communicate with my daughter, Hilda N. Petri, who is my lawyer and agent. Her address is P. O. Box 1096, Columbia, Missouri 65201. I am sure she will be sympathetic but I want to be sure about the legal aspects.</p>
<closer>
<salute>With all kind thoughts,</salute>


<signed>John G. Neihardt</signed>

<note>JGN:nh</note>
</closer>
</div1>
